Electrical Engineering (Ph. D Degree)





				Electrical Engineering (Ph. D Degree)
		


Programs Introduction
Last release date: Jul 13, 2017




Field of Study
Electrical & Elecronics Egnineering


Program Level
PHD


Semester
fall, spring


College
College of Electrical Engineering & Computer Science


Department
Electrical Engineering


Dead Line
2018-02-25


Media Language

50% ↑ in English



Chinese proficiency

						 No
											



Research Emphases
The Department of Electrical Engineering, National Taiwan University (NTUEE) has been ranked #1 in Taiwan since 1970 for admission of college students in the natural sciences and engineering, and has been long famous for its top-notch students and outstanding alumni. The department also possesses an outstanding faculty, among which there are 27 IEEE follows, 4 OSA fellows, 4 SPIE fellows, 1 ACM fellow and 1 Academician, etc. Each year, the department wins over 300 research grants/contracts and publishes more than 300 IEEE/SCI journal papers, an achievement comparable to top 10 EECS/ECE departments in the United States. In some research areas, the department holds top/dominant standing worldwide, such as microwave theories and technologies, integrated circuits and systems and electronic design automation etc., simply to name a few. With its long history of excellence in teaching, research and contributions/services to the society/industry, NTUEE is one of the most competitive EE departments in the world (within top 50 engineering and IT universities, US News and World Report 2008). 
The program of NTUEE is one of the most comprehensive among electrical-electronics-informatics-related departments over the world. The faculty’s expertise and courses cover 10 areas of EE, including Automatic Control, Power Systems/Power Electronics, Computer Science, Biomedical Engineering, Electro-Optics, Electromagnetic Waves, Communications and Signal Processing, Integrated Circuits and Systems, Nano-electronics, and Electronic Design Automation. Thus, NTUEE undergraduate students have the opportunity to expose themselves to many different divisions of the EE field.
The design of undergraduate coursework in NTUEE is first to provide students with broad and basic training in EE, such as electric circuits, electronics, electromagnetics, engineering mathematics, programming, and electronic circuit lab etc. After being equipped with enough basic knowledge, students can further explore/develop their own interest in specific subjects and professional areas by taking advantage a rich library of optional and advanced courses/labs in all different EE areas.
B.S. graduates from the department can further pursue their graduate/advanced studies in different EE areas within the NTU EECS College, by applying for the graduate programs of the EE department, Graduate Institute of Electronics Engineering, Graduate Institute of Communication Engineering, Graduate Institute of Photonics and Optoelectronics, or Graduate Institute of Biomedical Electronics and Bioinformatics. Overall, these provide diverse channels for students to further develop their professional expertise and careers.
Admission Requirements
語言證明文件
Proof of Language Proficiency	語言能力要求：非以英文為官方語言國家之申請者須提供等同托福英語能力IBT 80分（CBT 213分）以上證明。 
English Proficiency: A TOEFL score or the equivalent is required of all applicants whose first language is not English. The score should be IBT 80 (CBT 213) or above.
附加審查資料
Additional Application Documents	留學計畫書中請特別加強說明欲攻讀之領域（自動控制、計算機科學、電力系統與電力電子）
Please detail your area of study in your statement of purpose. (Automatic Control, Computer Science, or Power System/ Power Electronics)
